  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research contexts evaluating hemolysis prediction for centrifugal blood pump configurations. The CFD hemolysis model for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump was assessed under a reduced credibility framework. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors were reviewed; seven were formally assessed and six were scoped to not-assessed status pending further data. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was completed for primary flow parameters. The model has been applied in clinical research supporting ventricular assist device design decisions, and the assessment team concluded that credibility evidence was sufficient for the intended engineering use at the time of review. No structured Context of Use record is included in this Minimal-profile package; scope of intended use is conveyed through this narrative description only.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-experimental-hemolysis",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-cou2-monte-carlo-uq-results"
  ],
  "hasValidationResult": [
